text: Starting from the 21st October, there has been a continuous flow of chain swaps from tether-ethereum-ERC20 to tether-tron-TRC20. We thank @bitfinex for the effort, collaboration and support of #TRON community. You can read more here:

You realize my (DAO holdings / total ETH holdings) ratio was like 50x smaller than that of the average ETH community member, right? I continue to not understand people who literally think I was trying to hard-fork ethereum to save $19k.
A fuzzy and difficult-to-pin-down probability curve is definitely better than "at least X ETH and you've definitely deputized the ethereum community to help you protect your stuff at all costs!"

If you didn't like the 'China news pumped Bitcoin' narrative, then you are going to absolutely hate this: I think it's logical to expect that $NEO (china ethereum meme coin) has a much greater chance of outperforming now.

Rule based interventionism is a contradiction in terms, and yet it is a huge part of Ethereum's supposed value proposition. (If you have the power to intervene, you also have the power to stop following your own rules.)

The next step after shareholder capitalism is not “stakeholder capitalism” (death by a thousand vetos) but blockchain capitalism. Bitcoin and Ethereum have shown us a way to allow anyone to invest in a new technology, taking both risk and reward.
In addition to $BTC storing value for your users, as #Ethereum scales, you’ll have a whole decentralized finance playground to empower your users with as well. No need to build it all yourselves

Don't let your memes be dreams. Building a passionate and thriving culture around #Ethereum is just as critical as the technological developments, argued @MarkBeylin of @ethBounties in his talk from @EFDevcon.
